  "text": "Translation proceeds as follows. After Hiero translation with optimized feature weights and the first-pass language model, hypotheses are written to disk. For HCP we save translations as 10,000-best lists, whereas HiFST generates word lattices. The firstpass results are then rescored with the main 5-gram language model. In this operation the first-pass language model scores are removed before the main language model scores are applied. We then perform MBR rescoring. For the n-best lists we rescore the top 1,000 hypotheses using the negative sentence-level BLEU score as the loss function [CITATION_1] ; we have found that using a deeper k-best list is impractically slow. For the HiFST lattices we use lattice-based MBR search procedures described by [CITATION_2] in an implementation based on standard WFST operations [CITATION_3] ).",
